President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 8 pm on Monday. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 8 pm on Monday on developments in relation to the country’s response to the coronavirus pandemic. READ: COVID-19: SA records 17,421 new infections The address follows meetings of the National Coronavirus Command Council (NCCC), the President’s Coordinating Council (PCC) and Cabinet. President Ramaphosa also hosted a virtual engagement on Sunday between government and interfaith leaders on the COVID-19 Risk-Adjusted Strategy in an attempt to strengthen the national effort responding to the shifting pandemic